<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/8839> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #8839" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/7> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "p. 725" ;
	dprr:hasID 8839 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/815> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #815" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Praeposito in urbe, Liv. 8.36.1. Wrongly listed as Mag. Eq. in CIL 1\n     , 1, p. 351, Index. See Lübker no. 6." ;
	dprr:hasID 815 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/814> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #814" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "More probably the Consul of 336, who would be senior, than the Censor of 318." ;
	dprr:hasID 814 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/789> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #789" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 8.19.1; Diod. 17.82.1; Fast. Cap. (Papirius' name entire except Papi[r]ius); Chr. 354 (Crasso III et Venio); Fast. Hyd. (Crasso et Venoce); Chr. Pasc. ({Gr}); Cassiod.; Degrassi 34f., 108, 412f. They carried on the war with Privernum (Liv. 8.19-20). On Papirius, see Lübker no. 6, on Plautius, Münzer, APF 39f." ;
	dprr:hasID 789 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/788> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #788" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "The preservation of Papirius' name in Fast. Cap. enables us to distinguish the Consul of 336 and 330 (L. f. L. n.) from the Censor of 318 (L. f. M. n.). The Master of Horse in 320 was L. Papirius Cursor (Fast. Cap., Degrassi 34f., 108, 412f.), the Dictator of 325 and 324. These three Papirii have been confused in the Index of CIL 1(2), p.351; cf. Degrassi 539. In Livy Plautius' cognomen is clearly given as Venox. For Plautius Diod. has {Gr}." ;
	dprr:hasID 788 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/780> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #780" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Carried a bill to grant civitas sine suffragio to Acerrae (Liv. 8.17.12; cf. Vell. 1.14.4). See Lübker no. 6." ;
	dprr:hasID 780 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/779> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #779" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "L. Papirius Crassus, Cos. 336 and 330, who would normally be identified with this Praetor in a period when the praetorship frequently followed the consulship, was himself Praetor in 340. The other possibilities are L. Papirius Cursor, Cos. 326, 320, 319, 315, 313, and L. Papirius Crassus, Censor in 318. Cursor's praetorship is not otherwise attested, but if he held this praetorship we should have no evidence that the Censor of 318 ever held any curule office. Münzer (RE nos. 46 and 52) admits both possibilities." ;
	dprr:hasID 779 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/760> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #760" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cic. Fam. 9.21.2; Liv. 8.16.1; Diod. 17.29.1; Chr. 354 (Crasso et Hella); Fast. Hyd. (Crasso et Dulillo); Chr. Pasc. ({Gr}); Cassiod.; Degrassi 107, 410f. They carried on war with the Ausonii and the Sidicini (Liv. 8.16.1-3). See Lübker no. 6." ;
	dprr:hasID 760 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/759> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #759" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Papirius' name is given in full in Fast. Cap. on 330. For Duillius, Diod. has Kaeso Valerius." ;
	dprr:hasID 759 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/742> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #742" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 8.12.2. See Lübker no. 6." ;
	dprr:hasID 742 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/737> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #737" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Appointed during the illness of the Consul Torquatus to meet Antiate raids (Liv. 8.12.2-3; Cic. Fam. 9.21.2; Degrassi 107, 408f.). See Lübker no. 6." ;
	dprr:hasID 737 .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/736> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #736" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "On the name of Papirius, see Fast. Cap. on 330. On his accumulation of offices, see Mommsen, Str. 1.514, note 1; 2.146." ;
	dprr:hasID 736 .
